<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>PK done the right way</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Smeagol Vaca">Smeagol Vaca</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 12:18 p.m. 10/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> PK done the right way<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>How do you make a PK game that everyone enjoys? Heres an idea,how about you use zones.Lets say for example inside citys you cant PK, the guards wont let you.In the zones sorounding citys closely you cant PK either that will be the newbee training grounds, but then the areas farther away they will be the PK zones if you want to make a trip from one city to another the danger will be greatly increased therefore keeping the game fresh think about it, seeing for the first time Kalidim after 30th level becouse you had heard storys of the feirce bandits of the ButcherBlock Mountains, get it? And for those of you that realy wanted to go somewhere but your character was too low a level then there could be a sytem like the one with ships exept intead of boats it would be caravans and they would be driven by high level NPCs. Just a couple of ideas wich I believe implemented with some others will create the best ROLEPLAYING inviorment.

</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
